<br>
The idea of giving wizards a resist debuff in my opinion is ridiculous.  A little fyi here.  Resist debuffers do 1.5x normal when used in pvp.  A 60 fr cr debuff would be -90 to both.  This would essentially make resist gear for most melees utterly pointless vs wizards as we wouldn't be able to get enough to make a difference.<br>
<br>
Wizards allready  have a solution to high resists.  Lures.  They rightly pay a price for them in manna effeciency and cast time.<br>
<br>
Though that staff you mentioned does indeed need a change.  It needs to either have a cast time or a recast time to prevent a favorite strategy which is chain clicking it on someone to lag them out.  To balance that out make it unresistable so you don't NEED to chain cast to get it to stick.<br>
<br>
IC btw only does 730 or so dmg IF it hits for max. I wouldn't call IC much of a one shot kill even at the lvl that you get it between player hp and resists.<br>
<br>
Splurt isn't much of a one shot kill either as you can dispell it.<br>
<br>
Mannaburn on the other hand IS a true one shot kill. It's unresistable and few classes have enough hp to withstand it with cleric buffs let alone unbuffed.  See how there's a difference there? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/3/02 7:38:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=79>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A few notes.</span><hr size=1> Quote by Aerimus:<br>
